            <h1>CPMA Maxstats' Purpose:</h1>
            <p>This website was created for Professor Haderman's CS355 Databases Course during Spring 2015 at Sonoma State University.</p>
            <p>The purpose of CPMA Maxstats is to provide an intuitive and useful visual presentation of automatically generated one versus one match statistics for the competitive first-person shooter Quake III Arena. It has been designed for ease-of-use with a simple and clean layout. The goal is a relatively simple online match tracking and ranking system which allows for long term views of ingame performance.</p>
            <h2>About the author:</h2>
            <p>My name is Matt Smith and I have been playing competitive Quake since 2003. I have always wanted to make use of the the automatic statistics generation system available in the competition mod Challenge Promode Arena as very few websites have done so. I can be reached at irc.quakenet.org #uscpmpickup.</p>
